snippet.textDisplay:
Okay so my theory is that Soojin is the devil who was once an angel which showed her in white for a moment. Shuhua and Soyeon is actually one person. Shuhua was the angel version is Soyeon before Soojin pretended still be an angel seducing Shuhua to join her thus explains the whispering "ab imo pectore" meaning "from the bottom of my heart". Which shows how Shuhua suddenly changes into Soyeon when Soojin was pulling away after the whispering. Which also explains why Shuhua and Soyeon was at the same barbed wire place. Soyeon was then sent to a white room to be punished. Falling to Soojin's seduction, Soyeon fell into the temptation and went to hell which shows her in a black outfit dancing/celebrating with the demons or other corrupted souls. Soyeon was shown rolling around in what looks like red clay. Which is kind of like red wax which symbolizes "self-made" or "auto-gernerated" which means that the because she choose to be seduced by Soojin she had made herself into the person she is now. As she rolls around engrossed into the red clay meaning she has accepted who she has become.

Minnie is actually an innocent soul being dragged to be corrupted by Yuqi's orders. Which is why when Minnie tried to escape you can see Yuqi walking away as she sees an image of Soyeon accepting the descending Soojin seemingly envious of Soyeon. But then Miyeon, the Goddess, caught Yuqi and punished her as a fallen angel which explains why Yuqi was falling into the dark abyss. And image of fire burning was her wings being burnt off. Minnie tried her best to fight off the temptations of evil as they kept grabbing onto her which is why she has so many black hand prints on her clothes. Struggling to fight against evil has led Minnie exhausted and to break down as she was seen with a nose bleed and had fallen down. She decided to accept the temptations, letting it take over her (reason for why her arms are black) as she curls up trying to comfort herself. In the end, Minnie was sent to hell ended up in the same red clay as Soyeon once was in. Minnie just layed there helplessly, slowly accepting the way she has made herself to be.

snippet.textDisplay:
Line distribution is unfair?
If we think without "Oh my god..." parts:
0:01 Minnie
0:18 Soyeon
0:35 Yuqi
0:44 Miyeon
1:11 Soojin
1:28 Soyeon
1:46 Miyeon
1:54 Yuqi
2:20 Shuhua
3:02 Minnie
So Minnie, Soyeon, Yuqi, and Miyeon have 2 parts, Soojin and Shuhua have 1 part. They could give everyone "Oh my god" parts, but they didn't. They just gave Soyeon, Soojin, and Minnie. Maybe Miyeon and Yuqi's voice was a little deep for that part. And it's hard for Shuhua (she is still working on her accent and that note looks high for her). I don't know. But i felt like Miyeon can do that part too. I can imagine her singing that part. Whatever, the song is still BOP.

Can't help but notice how raw and exaggerated her moves are and how beautifuly she works with the camera! That scene in the red "mud" took my breath away!
